494
00:40:33,139 --> 00:40:35,552
Valdemar, I'm here.

495
00:40:36,184 --> 00:40:37,300
I'm with you.

496
00:40:38,227 --> 00:40:40,219
[Ernest] Help me.

497
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:43,647
What... What can I do?

498
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:47,105
[Ernest] Wake me.

499
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:51,272
- Wake you?
- [Ernest] I am dead.

500
00:40:52,742 --> 00:40:54,608
Let me go.

501
00:40:55,912 --> 00:40:59,576
Wake me and let me go.

502
00:41:03,002 --> 00:41:04,994
[birds twittering]

503
00:41:18,059 --> 00:41:19,971
Wake you? Of course.

504
00:41:21,729 --> 00:41:25,222
You're still... You're still hypnotized.
If I wake you...

505
00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:28,184
[Ernest] I will be released.

506
00:41:28,987 --> 00:41:32,480
Quickly. The others.

507
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:35,111
The others are coming.

508
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:39,574
I am part of both worlds.

509
00:41:40,373 --> 00:41:43,582
Theirs and yours.

510
00:41:43,668 --> 00:41:46,035
They want to use me

511
00:41:46,129 --> 00:41:48,086
to pass through.

512
00:41:48,172 --> 00:41:52,587
To pass through.
They're coming.

513
00:41:52,677 --> 00:41:56,091
Wake me.
Wake me before...

514
00:42:02,729 --> 00:42:03,729
It's over.

515
00:42:07,358 --> 00:42:08,358
It's finished.

516
00:42:16,325 --> 00:42:17,816
[Robert] How could you do this?

517
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:20,326
How in the hell
could you do this?

518
00:42:22,248 --> 00:42:24,285
What are we supposed
to do now, Jessica?

519
00:42:24,667 --> 00:42:26,750
How do we explain
two bullet holes in his body

520
00:42:26,836 --> 00:42:29,453
when he is supposed
to have died of natural causes?

521
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:31,960
We don't have to explain anything.
We're gonna bury him.

522
00:42:33,968 --> 00:42:36,255
- Bury him.
- In the woods, out back.

523
00:42:36,345 --> 00:42:37,345
Oh...

524
00:42:37,430 --> 00:42:40,093
We'll say we took him
somewhere else for the funeral.

525
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,842
- His hometown. Harrisburg.
- Oh, Christ.

526
00:42:42,935 --> 00:42:45,723
We have money, Robert.
It's just like you said.

527
00:42:46,355 --> 00:42:48,517
People won't ask
too many questions.

528
00:42:48,608 --> 00:42:51,396
They'll cooperate,
as long as there's enough money.

529
00:42:51,486 --> 00:42:54,229
I'm a living example of that.
God, I never should have...

530
00:42:54,322 --> 00:42:57,611
We have to bury him, Robert.
It's the only way to be rid of this.

531
00:43:02,038 --> 00:43:03,574
He asked me to...

532
00:43:04,916 --> 00:43:08,409
let him go, to wake him.

533
00:43:08,503 --> 00:43:12,122
He was not dead.
He couldn't have been dead.

534
00:43:12,757 --> 00:43:13,918
It's not possible.

535
00:43:14,675 --> 00:43:18,544
Somehow the hypnosis
kept him alive.

536
00:43:18,638 --> 00:43:20,254
What if he's still...

537
00:43:21,933 --> 00:43:22,933
How can we bury him

538
00:43:23,017 --> 00:43:26,010
- if there's still a chance that he might...
- We have no choice, Robert.

539
00:43:26,646 --> 00:43:28,262
We have no choice.

540
00:43:31,818 --> 00:43:33,150
You have no choice.

541
00:43:35,029 --> 00:43:37,149
If they find out about me,
they'll find out about you.

542
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:38,731
I'll deny it.

543
00:43:38,825 --> 00:43:41,158
[stammers]
I'll deny everything.

544
00:43:42,829 --> 00:43:44,491
Deny you talked to Pike?

545
00:43:44,580 --> 00:43:46,287
[thunderclap]

546
00:43:50,878 --> 00:43:52,961
[thunder rumbling]

547
00:43:53,047 --> 00:43:55,039
[shovel scraping]

548
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:07,559
[dog barking in distance]

549
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:22,775
[thunderclaps]

550
00:44:25,413 --> 00:44:27,905
[chorus vocalizing]

551
00:44:49,979 --> 00:44:52,392
- Robert?
- [thunderclap]

552
00:45:06,120 --> 00:45:08,203
[thunderclaps continue]

553
00:45:14,879 --> 00:45:17,212
- Robert?
- [thunderclap]

554
00:45:24,764 --> 00:45:26,255
Robert, is that you?

555
00:45:27,350 --> 00:45:32,812
[Ernest] They're coming for you,
Jessica.

556
00:45:33,564 --> 00:45:36,398
They're coming for you.

557
00:45:38,444 --> 00:45:40,902
They don't want me...

558
00:45:40,988 --> 00:45:45,574
to go into the ground.

559
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:46,660
Oh!

560
00:45:57,838 --> 00:46:00,205
[thunder rumbling]

561
00:46:13,854 --> 00:46:16,767
It isn't me, Jessica.

562
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:20,184
It's the others.

563
00:46:21,112 --> 00:46:22,648
[gunshot]

564
00:46:26,033 --> 00:46:29,777
It's the others, Jessica.

565
00:46:30,746 --> 00:46:33,614
Using my body.

566
00:46:33,708 --> 00:46:35,449
[gunshot]

567
00:46:37,545 --> 00:46:40,583
I asked you to help me.

568
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:44,458
You should have helped me.

569
00:46:45,678 --> 00:46:49,547
Now it's too late!

570
00:46:50,391 --> 00:46:53,850
[laughing]

571
00:47:06,907 --> 00:47:08,193
[gunshot]

572
00:47:08,826 --> 00:47:10,192
[moans]

573
00:47:11,996 --> 00:47:15,285
[laughing]

574
00:47:20,629 --> 00:47:22,370
[screams]

575
00:47:24,216 --> 00:47:25,832
[screams]

576
00:47:27,345 --> 00:47:28,711
[gunshot]

577
00:47:30,598 --> 00:47:32,464
[thunder rumbles]

578
00:47:52,828 --> 00:47:55,445
[Ernest laughing]

579
00:47:59,668 --> 00:48:02,752
[laughing continues]

580
00:48:06,675 --> 00:48:07,836
Valdemar.

581
00:48:08,386 --> 00:48:10,548
- I'm gonna wake you, Valdemar!
- [laughing]

582
00:48:10,638 --> 00:48:12,049
I'm gonna count to five.

583
00:48:13,432 --> 00:48:15,890
One! Two!

584
00:48:17,061 --> 00:48:19,804
- Three! Four!
- [laughing]

585
00:48:19,897 --> 00:48:21,729
Five!

586
00:48:21,816 --> 00:48:23,557
[laughing stops]

587
00:48:28,155 --> 00:48:29,817
[Ernest] It's too late.

588
00:48:31,409 --> 00:48:35,744
The others... [laughing]

589
00:48:35,830 --> 00:48:37,492
The others.

590
00:48:39,125 --> 00:48:42,664
Without me, they can't return.

591
00:48:42,753 --> 00:48:45,416
[laughing]

592
00:48:49,427 --> 00:48:52,591
They're with you now.

593
00:48:53,597 --> 00:48:56,340
They're with you.

594
00:49:26,255 --> 00:49:28,542
[wheels squeaking]

595
00:49:44,690 --> 00:49:46,773
- [thunder continues]
- [door opens]

596
00:49:46,859 --> 00:49:48,100
[door closes]

597
00:49:49,987 --> 00:49:52,900
[man] Come on. Let's go. Nice night...

598
00:49:54,575 --> 00:49:57,818
- Watch that umbrella.
- [man 2] Come on. We got one over here.

599
00:49:59,371 --> 00:50:01,863
[man] All right.
Let 'em through here. Let 'em through.

600
00:50:07,421 --> 00:50:09,083
[man 2] That's good right there.

601
00:50:12,468 --> 00:50:13,754
Come on.

602
00:50:23,354 --> 00:50:25,207
[detective] Guess she was
gonna bury him back here.

603
00:50:25,231 --> 00:50:27,439
She couldn't have dug
that grave by herself.

604
00:50:30,152 --> 00:50:32,485
We figure she popped him,
then shot herself.

605
00:50:33,489 --> 00:50:35,151
Very strange things though.

606
00:50:36,116 --> 00:50:38,073
We found blood in the freezer
down in the cellar.

607
00:50:38,160 --> 00:50:39,492
Christ.

608
00:50:40,996 --> 00:50:42,203
Rich people.

609
00:50:42,915 --> 00:50:45,453
The sick stuff always turns out
to be rich people.

610
00:50:47,127 --> 00:50:50,165
- She had him in the freezer, huh?
- [detective] That's what we think.

611
00:50:51,048 --> 00:50:53,415
- [thunder rumbles]
- [shutter clicks]

612
00:50:53,509 --> 00:50:55,421
And there was blood
in the freezer.

613
00:50:56,428 --> 00:50:58,385
So she had him down there
after he was shot.

614
00:50:58,472 --> 00:51:01,260
- Looks that way.
- So how'd he get up here?

615
00:51:01,850 --> 00:51:03,261
That's what we're asking ourselves.

616
00:51:04,186 --> 00:51:07,099
Wait. Wait till you get
a load of this.

617
00:51:12,361 --> 00:51:13,897
Oh, my God.

618
00:51:15,155 --> 00:51:17,147
This guy's been dead for weeks.

619
00:51:17,241 --> 00:51:19,198
[thunder rumbling]

620
00:51:19,285 --> 00:51:21,777
[metronome ticking]

621
00:51:26,834 --> 00:51:28,291
[ticking continues]

622
00:51:39,221 --> 00:51:42,214
[wind howling]

623
00:51:48,397 --> 00:51:51,606
[distorted voices, faint]

624
00:52:00,117 --> 00:52:02,404
[thunder continues]

625
00:52:11,503 --> 00:52:13,335
[ticking continues]

626
00:52:27,853 --> 00:52:29,845
[ticking continues]

627
00:52:42,951 --> 00:52:44,533
[tires screech]

628
00:52:49,833 --> 00:52:51,950
- Hey, 9-1-1?
- Yeah.

629
00:52:52,044 --> 00:52:56,209
It's god-awful. Screaming, crying,
like somebody's in some real pain.

630
00:52:57,007 --> 00:53:00,796
- How long's this been going on?
- A week. Two weeks maybe.

631
00:53:00,886 --> 00:53:03,754
Long enough to have the rest of us
in the building crazy over it.

632
00:53:04,223 --> 00:53:07,432
Couldn't get anyone to do anything
about it. You know how people are.

633
00:53:07,518 --> 00:53:09,475
Shit. It's driving me to drink.

634
00:53:09,937 --> 00:53:13,146
- I'm the guy who called 9-1-1.
- Well, you did the right thing.

635
00:53:18,278 --> 00:53:19,860
Police, Hoffman! Open up!

636
00:53:24,076 --> 00:53:25,783
[moaning]

637
00:53:26,704 --> 00:53:27,704
Hit it.

638
00:53:36,964 --> 00:53:38,080
Hoffman?

639
00:54:18,297 --> 00:54:21,961
What'd I tell you? Another rich guy.
Call in the troops.

640
00:54:23,135 --> 00:54:24,467
[uncocks gun]

641
00:54:45,783 --> 00:54:48,571
- [Robert moaning]
- [mouthing words]

642
00:54:49,536 --> 00:54:50,652
[Robert] Help.

643
00:54:51,371 --> 00:54:54,159
There's no one to wake me.

644
00:54:55,584 --> 00:54:57,951
No one to wake me.

645
00:54:58,045 --> 00:54:59,081
What?

646
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:03,131
Oh! Oh!

647
00:55:04,635 --> 00:55:07,252
- [gunshots]
- No!

648
00:55:08,847 --> 00:55:12,181
- Oh!
- [metronome ticking]

649
00:55:21,527 --> 00:55:24,190
[man narrating] <i>It's the depravity
that's in all of us.</i>

650
00:55:28,659 --> 00:55:32,278
<i>Perversity is one of
the prime impulses of the heart.</i>

651
00:55:32,830 --> 00:55:34,162
<i>Who's never done
something wrong</i>

652
00:55:34,248 --> 00:55:37,207
<i>- just because it was forbidden?</i>
- [man] Watch your step there.

653
00:55:37,292 --> 00:55:39,909
[narrator] <i>To be evil only
for the love of being evil.</i>

654
00:55:42,256 --> 00:55:45,169
Sir, do you think there's
any chance of me being transferred

655
00:55:45,259 --> 00:55:47,467
back to parking violations?

656
00:55:47,970 --> 00:55:50,963
- No. I... I don't want any dinner, O'Neill.
- [gags]

657
00:55:51,056 --> 00:55:52,843
Maybe just some coffee.

658
00:55:52,933 --> 00:55:55,892
[O'Neill]
No, sir. I was asking about a transfer.

659
00:55:55,978 --> 00:56:00,018
- Out. Oh, I'm real impressed. Out.
- [man] This is a pass to come in here.

660
00:56:00,107 --> 00:56:01,835
- Can you read English?
- [man 2] I can read English.

661
00:56:01,859 --> 00:56:04,087
I can read any language you want.
You don't come in with one of those.

662
00:56:04,111 --> 00:56:06,068
I want the police!
I want to see the police!

663
00:56:06,154 --> 00:56:08,758
[detective] What's the matter, Rod? You
having a little problem with the bouncer?

664
00:56:08,782 --> 00:56:10,301
- He's all right.
- There's the police.

665
00:56:10,325 --> 00:56:11,325
Be my guest.

666
00:56:16,623 --> 00:56:19,491
How is it you get sent down
on every one of these, huh?

667
00:56:20,085 --> 00:56:21,792
Still life is my specialty.

668
00:56:24,172 --> 00:56:25,379
- [beeping]
- Already get him?

669
00:56:25,841 --> 00:56:29,175
Yeah, this morning.
Bastard was asleep, right next to her.

670
00:56:29,261 --> 00:56:31,298
[camera shutter clicking rapidly]

671
00:56:31,889 --> 00:56:34,256
- So who was the first one on the scene?
- Valenz.

672
00:56:45,193 --> 00:56:47,401
[chattering]

673
00:56:50,824 --> 00:56:52,190
[shutter clicks]

674
00:56:55,329 --> 00:56:56,329
[man] Man! Oh!

675
00:56:57,456 --> 00:56:59,823
Hey, Usher. Who the hell
told you to pull that lever?

676
00:57:01,793 --> 00:57:04,536
You trying to get somebody killed?
Somebody stop this thing.

677
00:57:04,630 --> 00:57:06,997
- I'm sorry.
- [detective] You're sorry.

678
00:57:08,842 --> 00:57:10,834
[shutter clicking rapidly]

679
00:57:11,595 --> 00:57:13,086
Look at him taking pictures,
will ya?

680
00:57:13,180 --> 00:57:14,967
[chuckles]

681
00:57:15,057 --> 00:57:18,016
What's the big hurry, Usher?
Stiff's not going anywhere.

682
00:57:18,101 --> 00:57:19,433
[chuckles]

683
00:57:46,046 --> 00:57:47,253
[meows]

684
00:57:50,634 --> 00:57:54,048
- [purring]
- Where did you come from?

685
00:57:54,137 --> 00:57:56,049
[purring]

686
00:57:56,765 --> 00:57:58,927
- [meows]
- How did you get in here?

687
00:58:01,353 --> 00:58:03,686
Oh. You have to get off the paper.
Come on.

688
00:58:03,772 --> 00:58:06,731
[purring]

689
00:58:06,817 --> 00:58:09,309
How did you get in here?
How did you...

690
00:58:09,403 --> 00:58:11,019
[screeches]

691
00:58:12,990 --> 00:58:15,218
- What did you do to her?
- [Usher] What did I do to her?

692
00:58:15,242 --> 00:58:16,449
Look what she did to me.

693
00:58:16,535 --> 00:58:18,868
- [meows]
- Whose cat is it?

694
00:58:18,954 --> 00:58:22,197
- [meows]
- Did you scratch him?

695
00:58:22,833 --> 00:58:25,041
You mustn't do that.
He's very fragile.

696
00:58:25,127 --> 00:58:27,961
- Where did she come from?
- She's ours.

697
00:58:28,755 --> 00:58:30,246
I found her outside.

698
00:58:31,008 --> 00:58:34,422
You were so hungry, weren't you?
But I'll take care of you.

699
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:36,878
Isn't she pretty?

700
00:58:36,972 --> 00:58:38,658
She has a beautiful white spot
on her chest.

701
00:58:38,682 --> 00:58:39,889
[purring]

702
00:58:41,643 --> 00:58:42,683
We can keep her, can't we?

703
00:58:46,565 --> 00:58:47,726
Sure, honey.

704
00:58:48,233 --> 00:58:49,233
Good.

705
00:59:07,586 --> 00:59:11,796
[chanting in foreign language]

706
00:59:29,566 --> 00:59:31,558
[chanting continues]

707
00:59:33,820 --> 00:59:35,812
- [sighs]
- [chanting stops]

708
00:59:48,418 --> 00:59:50,330
- [woman] What is it?
- [Usher] The cat.

709
00:59:50,420 --> 00:59:53,413
- I think it's staring at me.
- [woman] My brave lover.

710
00:59:54,007 --> 00:59:56,819
Yeah, well, what if it decides to jump up
here in the middle of the night

711
00:59:56,843 --> 00:59:59,130
and claw my eyes out?

712
01:00:16,279 --> 01:00:17,861
[cat meowing]

713
01:00:21,618 --> 01:00:22,904
Better? Hmm?

714
01:00:23,620 --> 01:00:24,861
[snaps fingers]

715
01:00:38,969 --> 01:00:40,961
I can be brave when I have to.

716
01:00:42,973 --> 01:00:46,637
I see a lot of terrible things
in my work. You don't know.

717
01:00:48,019 --> 01:00:49,601
You're superstitious.

718
01:00:51,481 --> 01:00:53,188
I think it's 'cause she's
a black cat.

719
01:00:56,486 --> 01:00:59,729
You know where those superstitions began,
don't you? It was in the Middle Ages.

720
01:01:01,825 --> 01:01:05,614
Inquisitors burned women and black cats
'cause they thought they were witches.

721
01:01:05,704 --> 01:01:08,071
Finally, there weren't
many black cats left.

722
01:01:09,958 --> 01:01:12,450
Cats remember,
so they don't trust.

723
01:01:15,088 --> 01:01:17,922
[wind chimes clinking]

724
01:01:27,350 --> 01:01:29,888
[clinking continues]

725
01:01:37,903 --> 01:01:40,566
- [scratching]
- [meowing]

726
01:01:47,245 --> 01:01:49,282
[low growl]

727
01:01:55,754 --> 01:01:57,837
- [screeching]
- [gasps]

728
01:02:16,483 --> 01:02:19,317
[violins: classical]

729
01:02:21,655 --> 01:02:23,655
[woman] No, that's "B" natural.
- [music continues]

730
01:02:23,740 --> 01:02:24,740
- Good.
- [music stops]

731
01:02:24,824 --> 01:02:26,360
Try the whole thing
from the beginning.

732
01:02:27,577 --> 01:02:29,409
Three, four.

733
01:02:29,496 --> 01:02:32,580
[music resumes]

734
01:02:47,389 --> 01:02:50,132
[music continues]

735
01:03:05,573 --> 01:03:06,984
[music stops]

736
01:03:13,206 --> 01:03:15,166
- [imitates camera shutter clicking]
- [low growl]

737
01:03:18,586 --> 01:03:21,420
[music resumes]

738
01:03:27,846 --> 01:03:29,257
[low growl]

739
01:03:41,192 --> 01:03:42,728
[low growl]

740
01:03:43,361 --> 01:03:45,193
[screeches]

741
01:04:01,838 --> 01:04:03,079
[cat screeches]

742
01:04:10,138 --> 01:04:11,174
[screeches]

743
01:04:22,025 --> 01:04:23,937
What happened?
I heard her screaming.

744
01:04:24,027 --> 01:04:26,644
I accidentally caught her tail
in the door.

745
01:04:26,738 --> 01:04:28,946
She's all right.
By the way, what's her name?

746
01:04:29,949 --> 01:04:30,985
It's a secret.

747
01:04:32,202 --> 01:04:34,194
[laughs]

748
01:04:40,043 --> 01:04:41,079
Don't hurt her.

749
01:04:43,671 --> 01:04:46,334
