It looks like blood.

1010
01:31:10,340 --> 01:31:15,256
Oh, I... I cut my foot coming down...
coming down the stairs.

1011
01:31:15,345 --> 01:31:18,804
I didn't... didn't realize it.
Oh. Oh.

1012
01:31:19,224 --> 01:31:21,716
- I better take care of it. Good night.
- Yeah.

1013
01:31:22,268 --> 01:31:25,056
And, uh, don't forget
about the music. I mean...

1014
01:31:25,146 --> 01:31:26,432
- [Usher] Yes.
- Okay.

1015
01:31:29,693 --> 01:31:30,693
[music ends]

1016
01:31:31,987 --> 01:31:34,104
[Usher]
<i>"Life here has become ugly.</i>

1017
01:31:34,656 --> 01:31:35,772
<i>I'm leaving you.</i>

1018
01:31:36,825 --> 01:31:40,159
<i>I know enough of what has happened
to never want to see you again.</i>

1019
01:31:41,287 --> 01:31:43,028
<i>Do not look for me."</i>

1020
01:31:57,303 --> 01:32:00,717
<i>You wanted to leave me,
but now we're together forever.</i>

1021
01:32:21,286 --> 01:32:22,286
[doorbell rings]

1022
01:32:24,247 --> 01:32:26,159
Hi. I'm here for my lesson.

1023
01:32:26,249 --> 01:32:28,332
Not today.
We're leaving.

1024
01:32:29,210 --> 01:32:31,998
Leaving? But Annabel told me
I had a lesson...

1025
01:32:32,088 --> 01:32:35,126
She must have made a mistake.
We're going on a vacation.

1026
01:32:35,216 --> 01:32:36,752
- Well, can...
- 954? Mr. Usher?

1027
01:32:36,843 --> 01:32:39,551
- Come on in.
- Well, can I at least say good-bye?

1028
01:32:39,637 --> 01:32:42,095
She's sleeping. Just put it right there.

1029
01:32:42,182 --> 01:32:44,299
Make sure to be quiet.
Somebody's sleeping.

1030
01:32:45,727 --> 01:32:47,309
Quiet. Somebody's sleeping.

1031
01:32:52,650 --> 01:32:54,562
[horn honks]

1032
01:33:27,811 --> 01:33:29,723
[watch beeping]

1033
01:33:33,399 --> 01:33:36,813
Sorry about last night. Annabel and me...

1034
01:33:36,903 --> 01:33:41,238
Oh, for me? Oh, how sweet.

1035
01:33:42,200 --> 01:33:45,944
You know how it is.
We had an argument. Pfft.

1036
01:33:46,037 --> 01:33:48,620
- Oh, nothing serious, I hope.
- No.

1037
01:33:49,707 --> 01:33:52,144
As a matter of fact, we're going away
for a week to be alone together.

1038
01:33:52,168 --> 01:33:57,129
Oh, that'll be so nice. Annabel needs it.
She's been kind of gloomy

1039
01:33:57,215 --> 01:33:59,693
- ever since her cat disappeared.
- So we'll see you next week.

1040
01:33:59,717 --> 01:34:01,049
Say good-bye to Mr. Pym for me.

1041
01:34:01,136 --> 01:34:03,970
Oh, he'll be right back.
You can catch him before we go out.

1042
01:34:04,848 --> 01:34:05,848
You're going out?

1043
01:34:06,474 --> 01:34:09,137
My hubby's taking me
to the movies tonight.

1044
01:34:09,227 --> 01:34:10,843
We love the movies.

1045
01:35:20,340 --> 01:35:21,626
[horn honks]

1046
01:35:22,342 --> 01:35:23,503
[Usher] Mr. Pym.

1047
01:35:23,593 --> 01:35:25,321
- Mrs. Pym. See you next week.
- [Mrs. Pym] Oh, look.

1048
01:35:25,345 --> 01:35:27,962
- [groans] Ah!
- [laughs]

1049
01:35:29,933 --> 01:35:33,472
- The bastard!
- Come on. He's just trying to be friendly.

1050
01:35:33,561 --> 01:35:35,974
Imagine taking a vacation
in this weather.

1051
01:35:38,691 --> 01:35:41,775
[Usher] <i>They saw us leaving together.
Two witnesses.</i>

1052
01:35:42,403 --> 01:35:44,736
Nobody will think of looking
for you in the house.

1053
01:35:56,751 --> 01:35:59,710
[seagulls cawing]

1054
01:36:07,679 --> 01:36:11,673
Mister. Your drink.

1055
01:36:12,517 --> 01:36:13,758
Thanks.

1056
01:36:14,686 --> 01:36:17,770
- How's your wife feeling?
- Much better, thanks.

1057
01:36:18,523 --> 01:36:19,934
In fact, she's leaving today.

1058
01:36:20,024 --> 01:36:22,687
Nothing worse than getting sick
on your vacation, huh?

1059
01:36:22,777 --> 01:36:24,609
- Will you be eating here?
- Yes.

1060
01:36:25,113 --> 01:36:26,979
After I drop her off
at the station.

1061
01:36:44,007 --> 01:36:46,215
[phone rings]

1062
01:36:48,469 --> 01:36:50,961
[phone rings]

1063
01:37:00,648 --> 01:37:03,106
[phone rings]

1064
01:37:04,110 --> 01:37:07,148
- Hello.
- [dial tone humming]

1065
01:37:20,543 --> 01:37:23,001
[phone rings]

1066
01:37:27,467 --> 01:37:28,503
Hello.

1067
01:37:31,262 --> 01:37:34,255
- Hello!
- [dial tone humming]

1068
01:37:39,270 --> 01:37:40,556
[soft banging]

1069
01:38:48,172 --> 01:38:50,539
Hey, sorry. It's just me.
It's Christian.

1070
01:38:50,633 --> 01:38:53,842
- [Usher] What are you doing here?
- I left my violin.

1071
01:38:53,928 --> 01:38:56,341
I've been calling all week,
but nobody answered.

1072
01:38:56,431 --> 01:38:59,031
- And I need to practice, so I...
- Well, you got it. Now get out.

1073
01:38:59,100 --> 01:39:03,094
- All right. Where's Annabel?
- She's left.

1074
01:39:04,689 --> 01:39:06,125
She's gone on tour with
an orchestra.

1075
01:39:06,149 --> 01:39:08,516
She'll be gone for a while.
Two, three weeks.

1076
01:39:08,609 --> 01:39:10,521
- You have her address?
- No.

1077
01:39:10,611 --> 01:39:13,479
[phone rings]

1078
01:39:13,573 --> 01:39:15,610
She... She's traveling a lot.

1079
01:39:15,700 --> 01:39:17,987
[phone rings]

1080
01:39:18,077 --> 01:39:20,694
- Hello.
- [man] <i>Hi. Can I speak to Annabel?</i>

1081
01:39:20,788 --> 01:39:22,654
- Hmm?
<i>- She gave me this number.</i>

1082
01:39:22,748 --> 01:39:23,909
<i>Is she there?</i>

1083
01:39:25,168 --> 01:39:26,409
No, she's left.

1084
01:39:26,502 --> 01:39:30,792
<i>- I don't understand.</i>
- Who... Who is this? Did you call before?

1085
01:39:31,549 --> 01:39:33,791
- What do you want?
<i>- What do you mean, she's left?</i>

1086
01:39:34,260 --> 01:39:37,879
<i>I've been waiting for her in New York
for a week. I don't mean to pry, but...</i>

1087
01:39:37,972 --> 01:39:39,972
[shouting] What do you mean
you're waiting for her?

1088
01:39:40,808 --> 01:39:42,640
Who are you, her boyfriend or something?

1089
01:39:44,103 --> 01:39:46,595
Listen, asshole. You better listen to me.

1090
01:39:46,689 --> 01:39:50,603
Don't you ever
call this house again. Ever!

1091
01:39:50,943 --> 01:39:51,979
You hear me?

1092
01:39:54,363 --> 01:39:56,980
- That's strange.
- What?

1093
01:39:57,074 --> 01:40:00,074
Well, you think if she'd have gone
on tour, she would have taken her violin.

1094
01:40:02,830 --> 01:40:04,162
She has two.

1095
01:40:05,416 --> 01:40:07,936
Look, I heard what you were saying
to that guy on the telephone.

1096
01:40:08,586 --> 01:40:10,293
- I mean, if...
- What do you want?

1097
01:40:10,379 --> 01:40:12,939
You don't know anything,
so why don't you mind your own business.

1098
01:40:16,344 --> 01:40:17,835
And don't come back.

1099
01:40:20,515 --> 01:40:22,757
Oh, Mr. Usher.

1100
01:40:22,850 --> 01:40:24,432
- You're back.
- Just me.

1101
01:40:24,519 --> 01:40:26,226
Yeah, Annabel went on tour,

1102
01:40:26,312 --> 01:40:28,975
only she didn't take her violin
and she never got there.

1103
01:40:29,941 --> 01:40:33,059
Well, uh,
will she be away long?

1104
01:40:33,152 --> 01:40:36,236
Two or three months.
If they want her longer, who knows.

1105
01:40:36,322 --> 01:40:38,484
Don't listen to this guy.
He's a damned liar.

1106
01:40:39,200 --> 01:40:43,114
Well, I'll miss her. Your wife
and I love to talk together.

1107
01:40:43,204 --> 01:40:45,821
- You mean Annabel?
- Yes.

1108
01:40:46,832 --> 01:40:51,122
- She's not my wife.
- Oh? I-I thought...

1109
01:40:51,212 --> 01:40:53,532
We've lived together for four years,
but we're not married.

1110
01:40:54,090 --> 01:40:55,090
Oh.

1111
01:40:55,174 --> 01:40:58,918
Well, uh, come on, Gloria.
Excuse us.

1112
01:40:59,011 --> 01:41:00,218
Don't worry about it.

1113
01:41:03,516 --> 01:41:04,882
And you, stay away.

1114
01:41:05,977 --> 01:41:07,218
You're lying, man.

1115
01:41:12,650 --> 01:41:13,686
You're lying!

1116
01:41:15,611 --> 01:41:16,611
He's lying!

1117
01:41:18,489 --> 01:41:19,855
He knows where she is.

1118
01:41:35,631 --> 01:41:38,419
[object rattling]

1119
01:41:42,847 --> 01:41:45,840
[rattling continues]

1120
01:41:57,028 --> 01:41:58,940
[phone rings]

1121
01:42:01,991 --> 01:42:04,404
[scratching]

1122
01:42:07,288 --> 01:42:09,029
[scratching continues]

1123
01:42:13,461 --> 01:42:15,794
[phone rings]

1124
01:42:23,346 --> 01:42:25,303
I told you not to call back.

1125
01:42:34,690 --> 01:42:36,852
[scratching continues]

1126
01:42:59,507 --> 01:43:02,341
[scratching continues louder]

1127
01:43:14,271 --> 01:43:16,711
[Usher] <i>Must have gotten inside
while I was building the wall.</i>

1128
01:43:18,567 --> 01:43:19,774
[screeches]

1129
01:43:25,116 --> 01:43:27,699
[screeching continues]

1130
01:43:35,668 --> 01:43:37,910
[loud screeching]

1131
01:43:57,857 --> 01:44:00,395
Mr. Usher. Hi.

1132
01:44:01,277 --> 01:44:02,984
My name's Father Hammer.
I'm your neighbor.

1133
01:44:03,070 --> 01:44:04,070
Hello.

1134
01:44:06,157 --> 01:44:08,740
- It's leaking.
- Yeah, it's blood.

1135
01:44:08,826 --> 01:44:10,783
- [Hammer] Oh.
- [Usher] It's a rat.

1136
01:44:11,620 --> 01:44:14,454
- A big rat.
- Where did it come from?

1137
01:44:15,541 --> 01:44:17,703
It got into my house,
and I had to kill it.

1138
01:44:18,502 --> 01:44:22,371
Huge. I stabbed it a few times,
but, uh, it wouldn't die.

1139
01:44:22,465 --> 01:44:24,206
So I had to keep on stabbing it.

1140
01:44:25,593 --> 01:44:27,801
- You wanna take a look?
- No. Uh, thanks.

1141
01:44:27,887 --> 01:44:30,425
- I... I can't stand rats.
- [laughs]

1142
01:44:30,514 --> 01:44:31,880
I understand.

1143
01:45:11,263 --> 01:45:14,097
[no audible dialogue]

1144
01:45:17,144 --> 01:45:18,260
[Usher] "Murder."

1145
01:45:22,525 --> 01:45:23,936
Let him talk.

1146
01:45:29,490 --> 01:45:33,279
[doorbell ringing]

1147
01:45:40,793 --> 01:45:43,035
- [detective] Surprised?
- [Usher] Not really.

1148
01:45:43,128 --> 01:45:46,872
Not really? [laughs]

1149
01:45:46,966 --> 01:45:49,834
False accusations
are like the wind.

1150
01:45:51,595 --> 01:45:56,135
- At least I'm lucky they sent you.
- Yeah. Well, we'll see how lucky you are.

1151
01:45:56,225 --> 01:45:59,184
You know, Rod, they mentioned your name
down at the precinct, and I said,

1152
01:45:59,270 --> 01:46:03,731
- "I know that guy. He's an artiste."
- [laughs]

1153
01:46:03,816 --> 01:46:06,058
Let's not stand on ceremony.
Have a seat.

1154
01:46:06,151 --> 01:46:10,646
Oh, we like standing.
But we prefer walking. Check it out.

1155
01:46:13,576 --> 01:46:15,192
[rustling]

1156
01:46:15,286 --> 01:46:19,246
[sighs] I haven't had breakfast yet,
and I've got a lot of errands to run.

1157
01:46:19,331 --> 01:46:21,618
Hmm. Well, we won't be long.

1158
01:46:23,586 --> 01:46:25,202
[clicking phone cradle]

1159
01:46:27,298 --> 01:46:28,960
- Phone's unplugged.
- Oh.

1160
01:46:30,634 --> 01:46:34,048
There have been a lot of kook
calls since the book came out.

1161
01:46:34,138 --> 01:46:36,300
- Amateur photographers.
- [sneezes]

1162
01:46:36,390 --> 01:46:39,258
- God bless you.
- Is there a cat in here?

1163
01:46:41,353 --> 01:46:45,347
- There was one, but now it's gone.
- And what happened to it?

1164
01:46:46,317 --> 01:46:48,934
Don't tell me you're here
to search for a lost cat.

1165
01:46:49,028 --> 01:46:52,396
[chuckles]
I asked you something.

1166
01:46:52,489 --> 01:46:57,029
It was here for a few days,
and then it disappeared!

1167
01:46:57,119 --> 01:47:01,284
Disappeared, huh? Look,
speaking of disappearance, uh, Rod,

1168
01:47:01,373 --> 01:47:02,830
what happened to your wife?

1169
01:47:04,960 --> 01:47:06,041
She's not my wife.

1170
01:47:07,463 --> 01:47:11,628
[detective] Oh, right, right.
What was her name? Uh, Annabel.

1171
01:47:12,343 --> 01:47:15,051
What do you mean "was"?
It's still her name.

1172
01:47:15,971 --> 01:47:18,054
Well, past tense.

1173
01:47:18,140 --> 01:47:19,551
It's a bad habit.

1174
01:47:20,225 --> 01:47:23,309
It seems whenever you and I meet,
there's always a body around.

1175
01:47:41,372 --> 01:47:44,035
Okay, tell us where she is,
we'll have breakfast delivered.

1176
01:47:44,124 --> 01:47:46,912
I don't know! If I knew,
I'd tell you.

1177
01:47:52,383 --> 01:47:53,749
She left me.

1178
01:47:55,761 --> 01:47:58,253
We spent a couple
of days up at a lake.

1179
01:47:58,347 --> 01:48:00,179
We couldn't patch things up.

1180
01:48:01,642 --> 01:48:05,602
- She has a sister who lives in...
- No, her sister hasn't heard from her.

1181
01:48:06,981 --> 01:48:08,768
No wonder.
They don't like each other.

1182
01:48:18,242 --> 01:48:19,983
[sneezes] Excuse me.

1183
01:48:20,077 --> 01:48:23,912
That cat of yours must have
left a lot of fur behind, huh?

1184
01:48:26,041 --> 01:48:28,454
Say, this is the cat,
isn't it, Rod?

1185
01:48:31,505 --> 01:48:36,341
You know, Rod, they say that you... you
tortured this cat to get these pictures.

1186
01:48:37,302 --> 01:48:38,964
Now you wouldn't do that,
would you?

1187
01:48:39,680 --> 01:48:41,296
Say it isn't so, Rod.

1188
01:48:42,099 --> 01:48:43,260
It isn't so.

1189
01:48:44,059 --> 01:48:45,059
Good.

1190
01:48:45,644 --> 01:48:48,933
My kid has a couple
of little kittens. Loves 'em.

1191
01:48:49,648 --> 01:48:52,140
- Plays with 'em all the time.
- [man] Great, Legrand!

1192
01:48:52,234 --> 01:48:54,087
Have Rod take care of 'em
when you go on vacation.

1193
01:48:54,111 --> 01:48:55,602
[chuckles]

1194
01:48:56,613 --> 01:48:59,105
[phone rings]

1195
01:49:00,492 --> 01:49:02,654
- Hello.
- [Joseph] <i>This is Joseph.</i>

1196
01:49:02,745 --> 01:49:04,407
<i>I called yesterday
from New York.</i>

1197
01:49:06,081 --> 01:49:07,684
[British accent]
You wish to speak with Mr. Usher.

1198
01:49:07,708 --> 01:49:10,121
Sorry, Mr. Usher is not at home.

1199
01:49:10,210 --> 01:49:11,326
[hangs up]

1200
01:49:11,879 --> 01:49:13,523
[normal voice] Pain in the ass
won't leave me alone.

1201
01:49:13,547 --> 01:49:15,254
- Ah.
- Wants some of my pictures.

1202
01:49:15,340 --> 01:49:16,660
I have to get an unlisted number.

1203
01:49:16,717 --> 01:49:21,678
Ah. So Annabel and the cat took off, huh?
Didn't say where they were going, though.

1204
01:49:21,764 --> 01:49:24,598
Cats don't talk.
But Annabel left a note.

1205
01:49:25,142 --> 01:49:26,633
It's around here somewhere.

1206
01:49:39,239 --> 01:49:41,697
[chuckles]
Real love letter.

1207
01:49:41,784 --> 01:49:45,152
Why'd you tell the neighbors
that she was going on an orchestra tour?

1208
01:49:45,245 --> 01:49:48,864
I don't have to tell
those busybodies my business.

1209
01:49:48,957 --> 01:49:52,667
True. You got any letters of hers?

1210
01:49:52,753 --> 01:49:55,245
- This is her picture, isn't it?
- Yes.

1211
01:49:55,339 --> 01:49:57,752
- Do you mind if we take it?
- No.

1212
01:50:03,889 --> 01:50:06,973
Oh, and you could give me
the book as a present, huh?

1213
01:50:08,143 --> 01:50:09,143
[Usher] Sure.

1214
01:50:10,604 --> 01:50:13,267
- Thanks, Rod.
- You almost coauthored it with me.

1215
01:50:15,317 --> 01:50:19,607
Oh, one more thing. Um, where'd you
and Annabel go on this vacation of yours?

1216
01:50:19,696 --> 01:50:22,404
To Lake Arthur. I have a dual house
on the shore there.

1217
01:50:22,491 --> 01:50:26,110
Uh-huh. Okay, Rod, thank you.
Let's go.

1218
01:50:35,629 --> 01:50:38,121
Gentlemen, I'm glad
your suspicions have been allayed.

1219
01:50:38,215 --> 01:50:40,081
I wish you a long and happy life.

1220
01:50:41,718 --> 01:50:46,088
And what did you expect to find
between these solidly put-together walls?

1221
01:50:54,273 --> 01:50:56,856
[knocks]

1222
01:50:56,942 --> 01:50:58,683
[Legrand]
Open up. It's me again.

1223
01:50:58,777 --> 01:51:01,064
[knocking]

1224
01:51:04,867 --> 01:51:06,233
You forgot to sign it.

1225
01:51:15,294 --> 01:51:16,330
Ah.

1226
01:51:21,175 --> 01:51:23,292
That's funny. It was working
a minute ago.

1227
01:51:28,348 --> 01:51:30,431
I'm sure you got a pen inside.

1228
01:51:42,571 --> 01:51:44,779
Hey, Rod, I liked
what you said before

1229
01:51:44,865 --> 01:51:47,107
about me almost coauthoring
the book with you.

1230
01:51:47,201 --> 01:51:48,658
Would you sign it like that?

1231
01:51:54,208 --> 01:51:55,324
Yeah.

1232
01:51:57,878 --> 01:52:00,291
[cat screeching]

1233
01:52:00,380 --> 01:52:01,621
Where's that coming from?

1234
01:52:11,350 --> 01:52:13,433
[cat screeching]

1235
01:52:36,583 --> 01:52:40,293
[clattering]

1236
01:52:40,379 --> 01:52:42,746
- [shouting] What the fuck are you doing?
- Hold it.

1237
01:52:43,507 --> 01:52:44,793
What do you got?

1238
01:52:45,300 --> 01:52:47,337
[clattering stops]

1239
01:52:51,223 --> 01:52:52,259
Boss.

1240
01:53:08,699 --> 01:53:11,737
- It's fresh.
- What'd you say, Rod?

1241
01:53:11,827 --> 01:53:15,446
What'd we think we were gonna find
behind these solidly built walls?

1242
01:53:15,539 --> 01:53:17,496
A little guessing game, huh, Rod?

1243
